title: The Meeting
description: Tia and Tamera are twin sisters who were separated at birth and adopted; Tia by Lisa Landry, a fashion designer, and Tamera by Ray Campbell who owns a limo service. The girls tell of how they met each other in a shopping mall and how they were almost separated again.

title: First Dates
description: Tia and Tamera don't have anybody to go with to the school dance on Friday. They make a pact to each stay home on Friday night, but then Tamera gets asked out by a boy and accepts. Meanwhile, their parents, Lisa and Ray, have trouble adapting to living together.

title: Slumber Party
description: Tia and Tamera get to invite their friends over for a slumber party but get in trouble when one of the girls' boyfriends crashes the party. Meanwhile, Lisa has plans for a date that night but gets jilted at the last minute and has to spend the night at home with Ray.

title: Cheater, Cheater
description: Tia makes the honor roll at school, Tamera overhears Ray and Lisa discussing their kids and school and decides to make Ray proud of her by getting an A on her history test. On the day of the test, she blanks out and begs Tia to take the test as her to make the grade.

title: The Concert
description: The girls lose a contest for Cold Dog concert tickets and instead try to talk their parents into buying tickets for them. When Lisa and Ray hear the lyrics, they forbid the girls to listen to his music. But then Tia and Tamera win tickets to his concert and sneak out. Meanwhile, while Lisa and Ray are reminiscing on their high school days and high school crushes, they kiss, and then immediately freak out about it.

title: Hair Today
description: Lisa wins three certificates to a beauty spa makeover and takes the girls. Tia and Tamera try on a straight hairstyle which makes them a big hit. The next day at school, Tia goes back to her old look but Tamera keeps hers and gets in with the popular crowd. Meanwhile, Ray gets a new cappuccino maker and goes overboard on making and drinking cappuccinos.

title: Get a Job
description: The girls want to make extra money so look for work. Ray gets them jobs at his limo service but they quickly tire of cleaning limos with fat old men. They find open positions at a trendy restaurant, Rocket Burger, but don't want to hurt Ray so try to do both jobs at once.

title: Joey's Choice
description: Tia and Tamera both fall in love with the same boy who meets them both at Rocket Burger in different places and mistakenly believes they're the same girl. When he comes to pick her up for a date, he winds up taking both of them instead.

title: A Tall Tale
description: Tia and Tamera think they have the perfect dates for a dance, only to find their ideal dates are a couple of immature duds. Roger gets set up on a blind date with a beautiful girl, but when they meet he finds out she's much taller than he is.

title: Free Billy
description: Ray casts Tia and Tamera in a commercial for his limo service. At the shoot, they find a pig named Billy who is being horribly mistreated by his owner, so they sneak him out of the studio and take him home with them. Meanwhile, Lisa has a near death experience and tries to figure out the purpose behind her existence.

title: Operation: Deja View
description: Tia and Tamera are both taken to the hospital with appendicitis and rushed off to surgery. While they're in recovery, they find out from the doctor that they were born in the hospital and try to find the files on their real parents.

title: Two for the Road
description: Tia and Tamera get their driver's permits and their parents try to teach them to drive. Tamera is too carefree and Tia is too nervous, so Lisa and Ray decide to switch and each teach the other. However, this results in their cars crashing into each other, and the wreck scares Tia off from getting behind the wheel again; and even Lisa who is ordinarily so sure of everything, is shaken up by the experience.

description: Tia and Tamera get a scary lesson on the new medium of the Internet when they begin responding to chatroom posts from an individual named Verique.

title: Inherit the Twin
description: Tamera accuses Tia of distributing entries of her slam journal around school, resulting in a feud that has the two going to Student Court to settle their differences.

description: The twins believe they have met their biological father.
